http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Kochi/Dog-with-burn-injuries-rescued/article13981408.ece

Members of the Society for the Prevention of Cruelty to Animals (SPCA) rescued a dog found with more than 40 per cent burns.“The dog appeared to have been scalded with boiling water,” said SPCA district secretary T.K. Sajeev.He said the dog was found on the Vyttila-Kaniyampuzha Road and the Society was informed about the incident by a citizen.The dog was tranquilised and admitted at a city clinic.Mr. Sajeev said the SPCA was making an inquiry into the incident, and a police complaint would be filed based on the findings.